---
import Tally from '../components/Tally.astro'
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import '../styles/global.css'
---

<Layout>
	<div class="bg-light-gray mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-36 px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<!-- Hero Section -->
		<section class="space-y-6 text-center">
			<h1 class="text-charcoal text-4xl leading-tight font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
				Planning Center Doesn’t Have to Be <span class="border-gold border-b-4">Overwhelming</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 sm:text-xl">
				If you feel like you're constantly fixing Planning Center instead of using it, you're not
				alone. I’ll show you what to fix first and how to get clarity fast.
			</p>
			<div class="mt-10">
				<Tally url="https://tally.so/r/wogXxX" label="Send Me the Info" />
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Problem Section -->
		<section class="bg-sage space-y-6 rounded-xl px-6 py-12 text-center">
			<h2 class="text-navy text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-balance sm:text-3xl">
				Planning Center shouldn't feel like a second job.
			</h2>
			<p class="text-charcoal mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-balance sm:text-xl">
				From scattered data to missed follow-ups, it's easy to get stuck in admin quicksand.
			</p>
			<div class="flex justify-center">
				<ul class="text-charcoal mt-8 space-y-5 text-left text-base">
					<li class="flex items-center gap-4">
						<i data-lucide="alert-triangle" class="text-navy h-6 w-6"></i>
						<span>Worried people are falling through the cracks</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-center gap-4">
						<i data-lucide="help-circle" class="text-navy h-6 w-6"></i>
						<span>Not sure if you’re using PCO the right way</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-center gap-4">
						<i data-lucide="clock" class="text-navy h-6 w-6"></i>
						<span>Wasting hours on what should be automatic</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-center gap-4">
						<i data-lucide="user-minus" class="text-navy h-6 w-6"></i>
						<span>Volunteers falling off without notice</span>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Empathy/Authority Section -->
		<section class="space-y-6 text-center">
			<h2 class="text-navy text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-balance sm:text-3xl">
				You’re not doing anything wrong—this stuff is just messy.
			</h2>
			<p class="text-charcoal mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-balance sm:text-xl">
				I’ve spent years cleaning up Planning Center chaos. Now I help churches create systems that
				save time and support ministry—not sabotage it.
			</p>
		</section>

		<!-- Plan Section -->
		<section class="space-y-10 text-center">
			<h2 class="text-navy text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">
				A simple path to clarity
			</h2>
			<p class="text-charcoal mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed sm:text-xl">
				No need to start from scratch. I’ll help you focus on what matters most, right now.
			</p>

			<div
				class="mx-auto grid max-w-sm gap-15 sm:grid-cols-1 md:max-w-none md:grid-cols-3 md:gap-2"
			>
				<!-- Step 1 -->
				<div
					class="border-sage hover:border-gold rounded-2xl border bg-white p-6 text-left shadow-sm transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:shadow-lg"
				>
					<div
						class="bg-sage mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-md"
					>
						<i data-lucide="calendar" class="text-charcoal h-6 w-6"></i>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-charcoal text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">Submit Your Email</h3>
					<p class="text-charcoal mt-2">I’ll send you the overview + next steps.</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Step 2 -->
				<div
					class="border-sage hover:border-gold rounded-2xl border bg-white p-6 text-left shadow-sm transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:shadow-lg"
				>
					<div
						class="bg-sage mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-md"
					>
						<i data-lucide="search-check" class="text-charcoal h-6 w-6"></i>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-charcoal text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">Get a Simple Breakdown</h3>
					<p class="text-charcoal mt-2">
						Understand the 1–3 things that will make the biggest difference right away.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Step 3 -->
				<div
					class="border-sage hover:border-gold rounded-2xl border bg-white p-6 text-left shadow-sm transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:shadow-lg"
				>
					<div
						class="bg-sage mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full shadow-md"
					>
						<i data-lucide="file-text" class="text-charcoal h-6 w-6"></i>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-charcoal text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">Move Forward with Clarity</h3>
					<p class="text-charcoal mt-2">
						Use the info to DIY or explore working together—your call.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<p class="text-charcoal mx-auto mt-12 max-w-2xl italic">
				This isn’t a sales trap. It’s clarity, first—so you can decide if you want help or not.
			</p>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ Section -->
		<section class="space-y-10 text-center">
			<h2 class="text-charcoal text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">
				Frequently Asked Questions
			</h2>

			<div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl space-y-6 text-left text-gray-700">
				<details class="group border-sage border-b py-4">
					<summary
						class="text-charcoal flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between text-lg font-medium"
					>
						What exactly is included in the Planning Center Health Check?
						<i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="h-5 w-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
						></i>
					</summary>
					<p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
						You'll get a 60-minute recorded Zoom session, a full Loom follow-up video with your top
						fixes, a Notion dashboard with all recommendations, and 7 days of follow-up Q&A by
						email. It’s designed to deliver immediate value—even if you don’t hire help afterward.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details class="group border-sage border-b py-4">
					<summary
						class="text-charcoal flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between text-lg font-medium"
					>
						Who is this best suited for?
						<i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="h-5 w-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
						></i>
					</summary>
					<p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
						Churches who feel lost inside Planning Center, have inherited a messy setup, or just
						want to finally understand how to use it the right way. Whether you're new to PCO or
						just never had time to optimize it, this call will give you clarity fast.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details class="group border-sage border-b py-4">
					<summary
						class="text-charcoal flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between text-lg font-medium"
					>
						Is there a cost?
						<i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="h-5 w-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
						></i>
					</summary>
					<p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
						Yes. The full Health Check session is a one-time $300 investment. Churches often tell me
						the insights from this call save them weeks—if not months—of spinning their wheels. It’s
						a simple, practical way to get expert eyes on your setup without a long-term commitment.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details class="group border-sage border-b py-4">
					<summary
						class="text-charcoal flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between text-lg font-medium"
					>
						Do I have to commit to anything else?
						<i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="h-5 w-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
						></i>
					</summary>
					<p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
						Nope. There’s no pitch at the end. This is designed to give you clarity first. If we
						both feel like working together makes sense after the call, we can talk—but that’s
						totally up to you.
					</p>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- CTA Section -->
		<section class="bg-sage text-charcoal rounded-xl px-6 py-16 text-center shadow-lg">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Want to see what’s possible?</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 text-lg sm:text-xl">
				I'll send over the breakdown and you can decide if a deeper audit makes sense.
			</p>
			<div class="mt-8">
				<Tally url="https://tally.so/r/wogXxX" label="Send Me the Info" />
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
</Layout>
